FBIS3-16275 "drsov050_b_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Poll Shows Majority Consider Amnesty Wrong PM1503085594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 12 Mar 94 p 4 PM1503085594 Moscow IZVESTIYA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "`Opinion' of the Amnesty"] [Text] The "Opinion" service (leader Gr. Pashkov) carried out a telephone poll 4-6 March. There were 1,100 respondents. The sample is representative in terms of sex, age, level of education, and main types of work: Do you think that the State Duma acted rightly or wrongly in declaring an amnesty for those who participated in the events of August 1991 and October 1993? Wrongly -- 56.9 Don't know -- 21.8 Do you think that following the amnesty the political situation in our country will improve, deteriorate, or stay the same? Improve -- 6.1 Deteriorate -- 43.6 Stay the same -- 28.2 Don't know -- 22.1 What punishment do you think 1) the members of the State Committee for the State of Emergency, 2) Rutskoy, and 3) Khasbulatov, deserve? ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |1) |2) |3) | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |None |21.5 |17.5 |14.8 | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Pardon |5.9 |6.5 |6.4 | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Suspended custodi-|9.8 |8.0 |8.7 | |al sentence | | | | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Up to five years' |9.9 |9.7 |11.0 | |imprisonment | | | | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Up to 10 years |6.8 |8.1 |9.7 | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Over 10 years |5.1 |6.5 |7.1 | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Life imprisonment |2.5 |4.6 |4.1 | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Death sentence |2.5 |3.4 |3.3 | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Don't know |36.0 |35.7 |34.9 | -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
